<span class="displaytext">washington, dc -- "with the white house now acknowledging a direct role in the justice department's u.s. attorney firings, the president must affirmatively step forward to explain what he is doing to address the politicization of our prosecutorial system and what role he and his aides played in this controversy. <p>"the president is the chief executive of the country and this matter goes to the heart of his ability to manage our federal law enforcement and u.s. attorney system. it is imperative that the president act swiftly to explain what role the white house played in this situation, hold those who acted inappropriately accountable, and take responsibility."</p></span>



